Subject: [PATCH 23/24] =?UTF-8?q?fix(m135):=20Path=20B=20build=20fixes=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20disable=20b64=20text=20capture?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Surgical fixes to make headless_shell link under M135. Path B per
roctinam/carbonyl#27 — disables the b64 text-capture path which
reaches into blink/renderer/core internals from a non-blink TU and
triggers an Oilpan/cppgc cascade. Path A (#28) extracts text capture
into a real blink TU and is the structural fix.

Fixes by file:

- content/renderer/render_frame_impl.cc:
  - Drop blink/renderer/core includes (cppgc cascade trigger)
  - Wrap TextCaptureDevice class in #if 0
  - Wrap render_callback_ lambda + ObserveTerminalRender in #if 0
  - Guard render_callback_.get() deref against null
  - Fix onDrawGlyphRunList override (3 args, not 4)
  - browser_interface_broker_proxy_ -> GetBrowserInterfaceBroker()
  - [=] -> [=, this] (deprecated capture)

- headless/lib/browser/headless_screen.{cc,h}:
  - Bridge::GetSize() doesn't exist; use Renderer::GetCurrent()->GetSize()
  - IsNaturalPortrait moved from protected to public

- headless/lib/browser/headless_browser_impl.cc:
  - content::NativeWebKeyboardEvent -> input::NativeWebKeyboardEvent
  - [=] -> [=, this] (deprecated capture)
  - [[maybe_unused]] on kDefaultWindowSize / kDefaultFontRenderHinting

- components/viz/service/display_embedder/software_output_device_proxy.cc:
  - Drop output_device_backing.h include (Windows-only in M135)
  - CreatePlatformCanvasWithPixels: pass new bytes_per_row=0 arg

- third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.cc:
  - FontFamily::SetFamily removed; use constructor

- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fonts/font.cc:
  - Construct TextRunPaintInfo locally (no longer a function param)

- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/graphics_context.h:
  - [[maybe_unused]] on disable_destruction_checks_

- third_party/blink/renderer/bindings/core/v8/script_promise_resolver.cc:
  - Restore empty Dispose() body (header still declares it under
    DCHECK_IS_ON; carbonyl patch had removed the definition entirely)

See: roctinam/carbonyl#27
